# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the real value. `.env` is gitignored.
#
# Google Cloud Translation API key. Used ONLY at build time by
# `scripts/translate.js` (run via `pnpm run translate`). It must stay
# server-side: do NOT rename it with a PUBLIC_ prefix, or Astro will expose it
# to the client browser.
#
# In Cloudflare production this is supplied separately as an encrypted secret:
#   wrangler secret put GOOGLE_TRANSLATE_API_KEY
GOOGLE_TRANSLATE_API_KEY=

# ── Google AdSense (optional, off by default) ────────────────────────────────
# Leave EMPTY to ship the site ad-free. The whole ad system is dormant until
# this holds a real publisher id. When the site has a handful of users and is
# approved by AdSense, set this to your id (format: ca-pub-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX).
#
# Unlike the translate key above, this one IS prefixed PUBLIC_ on purpose: the
# AdSense client id is not a secret (it ships in the loader URL on every ad
# page), and Astro only exposes PUBLIC_-prefixed vars to the browser bundle.
#
# After setting it, also: (1) fill public/ads.txt with the matching pub- line,
# and (2) add <AdSlot slot="..." /> where you want ads. CSP is already prepared.
# In Cloudflare, set it as a build/var too so the production bundle picks it up.
PUBLIC_ADSENSE_CLIENT=
